      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 2112: After the retry budget is exhausted, identityRetryState_ is reset. If identityAnnouncedCb is invoked again with ok\u003dfalse later, a fresh IdentityRetryState is created and the same 3 retries are scheduled again, so the code does not actually \u0027give up\u0027 across repeated announcement failures. This can create unbounded retry cycles under persistent network/server failure. Preserve an exhausted state or add a separate cooldown/backoff before recreating retry state.\n```suggestion\nif (state.attempt \u003e\u003d IdentityRetryState::maxAttempts) {\n    JAMI_ERROR(\"[Account {}] Identity announcement failed after {} retries, giving up\",\n               getAccountID(), state.attempt);\n    return;\n}\n```",
