      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 2707: The 30s debounce is keyed only on the last refresh time, so a connectivityChanged() event while the DHT is already running can update lastPresenceRefresh_ and then suppress the refresh needed immediately after a later reconnect/GSM standby recovery. That makes the fix timing-dependent and can leave buddy presence unsubscribed for up to 30s or indefinitely if no later event occurs. Gate the debounce to actual DHT restart/reconnect state, or always perform the first refresh after a disconnected-to-running transition and debounce only subsequent churn.\n```suggestion\nif (presenceManager_ \u0026\u0026 dht_ \u0026\u0026 dht_-\u003eisRunning()) {\n    const auto now \u003d std::chrono::steady_clock::now();\n    if (!presenceRefreshDoneSinceDisconnect_\n        || now - lastPresenceRefresh_ \u003e\u003d std::chrono::seconds(30)) {\n        presenceRefreshDoneSinceDisconnect_ \u003d true;\n        lastPresenceRefresh_ \u003d now;\n        presenceManager_-\u003erefresh();\n    }\n}\n```\nReset presenceRefreshDoneSinceDisconnect_ when the account/DHT is observed disconnected.",
